      "comment_id" : 95207695,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "<code>never()</code> is not significantly more readable than <code>times(0)</code>. But the existence of <code>never</code> does increase cognitive load and makes the mockito system harder to understand and remember how to use. So really mockito shouldn&#39;t have included <code>never</code> in their API, its not worth the mental cost."
