    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As a more general pattern to follow, I tend to use an <code>@After</code> block in the test:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@After\npublic void after() {\n    verifyNoMoreInteractions(&lt;your mock1&gt;, &lt;your mock2&gt;...);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Then the test is free to verify only what <em>should</em> be called.</p>\n\n<p>Also, I found that I often forgot to check for \"no interactions\", only to later discover that things were being called that shouldn't have been.</p>\n\n<p>So I find this pattern useful for catching all unexpected calls that haven't specifically been verified.</p>\n"
  }, {
