    "question_id" : 12862659,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just as a suggestion, if you want to be more aligned at syntax level with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavior-driven_development\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Behavior-driven development</a> style there is <a href=\"https://javadoc.io/static/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.4.0/org/mockito/BDDMockito.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">BDDMockito</a>:</p>\n<p>You could use:</p>\n<pre><code>then(dependency).should(never()).someMethod();\n</code></pre>\n<p>As an equivalent replacement of:</p>\n<pre><code>verify(dependency, never()).someMethod();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1628102,
      "reputation" : 5215,
      "user_id" : 1503163,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c849158de87c316eccc01649e521374a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Sanjay Bharwani",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1503163/sanjay-bharwani"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1685967795,
    "creation_date" : 1685967795,
    "answer_id" : 76406378,
    "question_id" : 12862659,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Couple of options to do that depending on the use case.</p>\n<p>If you want to verify that <code>someMethod</code> is not invoked on <code>dependency</code> use below</p>\n<pre><code>verify(dependency, times(0)).someMethod();\n</code></pre>\n<p>or much better readable option</p>\n<pre><code>verify(dependency, never()).someMethod();\n</code></pre>\n<p>If you want that no interaction on specific dependency to happen, then use below.</p>\n<pre><code>verifyNoInteractions(dependency);\n</code></pre>\n<p>If there are multiple methods on a dependency and you want to make sure only expected method is invoked and nothing else. Then use</p>\n<pre><code>verify(dependency, times(1)).someMethod();\nverifyNoMoreInteractions(dependency);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
